Frequently Asked Questions

What is the median home price in Los Angeles?
Homes for sale in Los Angeles have a median listing price of $980K. Some of these homes are Hot Homes, meaning they're likely to sell quickly.
How long do homes stay on the market in Los Angeles?
Most homes for sale in Los Angeles stay on the market for 67 days and receive 6 offers. In the past month, 6077 homes have been sold in Los Angeles. The median price per square foot in Los Angeles has increased by 11.0% over the past year.
What are some of the most popular neighborhoods in Los Angeles?
Popular neighborhoods include Pacific Palisades, Encino, Tarzana, Studio City, Granada Hills, La Caada Flintridge, Sherman Oaks, Chatsworth, Northridge, North Hollywood, Sunland-Tujunga, Sylmar, Manhattan Beach, West Hills, and Woodland Hills.
